textile_editor
==============

Simple textarea enhancement with textile syntax. Only one js file required.

Requires jQuery version 1.4+



Installation
============

The following line must be placed after the jquery inclusion. The 'defer' attribute is not required.

<%= javascript_include_tag 'textile_editor', :defer => 'defer' %>



Usage
=====

Add class "textile_editor" to any textarea that you would like to have the editor enabled on.


Given the following markup:

  <p>
    <label>Description:</label>
  </p>

  <p>
    <textarea class="textile_editor"></textarea>
  </p>


Enabling the textile editor will produce the following markup:

  <p>
    <label>Description:</label>
  </p>

  <p class="textile_editor_buttons">
    <input type="button" value="B" style="font-weight: bold;" />
    <input type="button" value="I" style="font-style: italic;" />
    <input type="button" value="U" style="text-decoration: underline;" />
    <input type="button" value="D" style="text-decoration: line-through;" />
    <input type="button" value="link" style="color: #00a; text-decoration: underline;" />
    <input type="button" value="h1" style="font-weight: bold;" />
    <input type="button" value="h2" style="font-weight: bold;" />
    <input type="button" value="h3" style="font-weight: bold;" />
    <input type="button" value="”" />
  </p>
  
  <p>
    <textarea class="textile_editor"></textarea>
  </p>



Available keyboard shortcuts:

  CTRL + B - bolded text
  CTRL + I - italic text
  CTRL + U - underlined text
  CTRL + D - stroked text
  CTRL + L - instert link


